   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Fair Finance Asia 2018-2022</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">Fair Finance Asia 2018-2022</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="SV">Omprogrammerade medel f&#xF6;r att lindra konsekvenserna av covid-19
Fair Finance Asia programmet syftar till att minska negativa effekter av investeringar i Asien vad g&#xE4;ller m&#xE4;nskliga r&#xE4;ttigheter, milj&#xF6; och klimat samt &#xF6;ka investeringar som gynnar fattigdomsminskning och inkluderande ekonomisk utveckling. 

Projektets m&#xE5;l &#xE4;r en h&#xE5;llbar finanssektor i Asien, med finanssektorsinstitutioner verksamma p&#xE5; nationell och regional niv&#xE5; som &#xE4;r mer transparenta och tar ansvar f&#xF6;r samt respekterar m&#xE4;nskliga r&#xE4;ttigheter och milj&#xF6;, social, och styrnings kriterier (p&#xE5; engelska: Human Rights (HR) and Environment, Social, and Governance (ESG) criteria).</narrative>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Reprogrammed funds to mitigate the impact of COVID-19
The Fair Finance Asia programme focuses on reducing the negative impact of investments in Asia on human rights, the environment and climate change, and increasing investments in pro-poor inclusive economic development. The cross-border nature of the problem requires an approach targeting both national and regional level.

The programme&apos;s intended outcome is a sustainable finance sector in Asia, with financial sector institutions operating at national and regional level being more transparent and accountable and adhering to Human Rights (HR) and Environment, Social, and Governance (ESG) criteria.</narrative>
  </description>
